HOW TO RUN THIS
======================================
1. If you dont have gem bundler:
  gem install bundler
 
2. Install gems:
  bundle install

  If you have troubles installing pg gem:
    Edit this PATH to match your pg install location
      export PATH=/usr/local/psql/bin:$PATH

    Depending on which ruby interpreter you have, select one.
      export ARCHFLAGS='-arch i386'
      export ARCHFLAGS='-arch x86_64'

3. Create your config/database.yml basing on database.yml.example

4. Create and migrate db:
  rake db:create:all
  rake db:migrate

5. Run script for downloading mpk.czest.pl html files:
  mkdir tmp
  ruby vendor/pack_downloader.rb

6. Run script for html parsing (this may take some time):
  ruby vendor/initial_html_data_extractor.rb extract
